This paper is about improving the efficiency of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for real-time performance. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture for CNNs, which involves combining different techniques from existing architectures, such as ResNet, DenseNet, and ShuffleNet. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also focuses on optimizing the efficiency of the model, which could fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments with open source datasets, which could suggest that it belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
